&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Firm Overview&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FT Partners is a leading boutique investment bank exclusively focused on the Financial Technology sector. Headquartered in San Francisco with offices in New York and London, the firm has advised on many of the most significant and high-profile transactions in global FinTech.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FT Partners provides a full suite of strategic advisory services, including M&amp;amp;A advisory, private capital raising, and capital markets advisory. With a 250+ banker global platform, the firm is widely recognized as the dominant advisor in one of the most dynamic and high-growth industry sectors. FT Partners combines senior-level attention, execution excellence, and unmatched sector expertise to deliver superlative outcomes for high-growth and scaled market leaders alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Role Description&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SpecialX is FT Partners’ dedicated financial and strategic execution arm. We work alongside the investment banking teams, but our focus is distinct: ensuring that financial analysis, growth positioning, and investor materials are fully prepared to withstand sophisticated private equity and strategic buyer scrutiny.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is an oversight-heavy, forward-looking role at the center of live transactions. The Associate will help shape how high-growth FinTech companies articulate and defend their growth story to the most sophisticated investors in the market. Rather than simply analyzing performance, this role advises on how growth should be projected, how risks should be framed, and how the financial narrative is constructed to align with how investors underwrite businesses. It requires strong financial judgment, intellectual confidence, and the ability to move seamlessly between detailed execution and strategic advisory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Associate will work directly with senior bankers and firm leadership, gaining meaningful exposure to transaction strategy and investor positioning at the highest levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own critical financial and growth workstreams across live deals, including revenue quality, cohort &amp;amp; retention analysis, unit economics, sales efficiency, and growth validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise bankers and management teams on how growth should be modeled, projected, and defended in front of sophisticated investors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and frame the key issues that will drive investor scrutiny, surfacing risks and shaping mitigation strategies before diligence begins&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with visibility across multiple transactions, balancing deep execution on select deals with high-level oversight across broader live activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and reinforce high standards of analytical rigor and investor-grade thinking across the team, including mentorship of junior professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help strengthen and institutionalize SpecialX as a differentiated strategic capability within FT Partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
